BicycleExchange
Database Design Document
Version 1.0  |  March 2026

1. Overview
BicycleExchange is a peer-to-peer used bicycle marketplace platform that supports both online listings and physical marketplace events. The database is hosted on Supabase (PostgreSQL) and consists of 20 tables organized into six functional groups: User & Authentication, Bicycle Catalog, Listings & Wishlist, Events, Transaction Lifecycle, and Platform Management.

2. Database Summary
The following table provides a high-level summary of all 20 tables in the schema.

Table Name	Group	Purpose
users	User & Auth	All platform users: buyers, sellers, inspectors, admins
wallet	User & Auth	User balance wallet (1-to-1 with users)
wallet_transaction	User & Auth	Ledger of all wallet balance changes
invalidate_token	User & Auth	Blacklisted JWT tokens for logout enforcement
brand	Bicycle Catalog	Bicycle brand reference table
category	Bicycle Catalog	Bicycle category reference table
bicycle	Bicycle Catalog	Physical bicycle asset specifications
bicycle_library	Bicycle Catalog	Standard model reference library
bike_listing	Listings	Marketplace sale listings posted by sellers
wishlist	Listings	User saved/favorited listings
events	Events	Physical marketplace events organized by admins
event_bicycle	Events	Bicycles registered for a specific event
event_inspector	Events	Inspector assignments to events
deposit	Transactions	Buyer deposit payments for reservations
reservation	Transactions	Confirmed buyer-seller meeting reservations
check_in	Transactions	Physical check-in records at meeting point
transaction	Transactions	Final sale transaction records
dispute	Transactions	Buyer/seller disputes on transactions
inspection_report	Transactions	Inspector evaluation reports
system_config	Platform Mgmt	Platform-wide configuration key-value store

3. Key Relationships
The schema follows a hub-and-spoke model centered around the users, bike_listing, and events tables. Below are the primary relationship chains that drive the transaction lifecycle:

Relationship	Type	Description
users -> wallet	1 : 1	Each user has exactly one wallet
users -> bike_listing	1 : N	A seller can post multiple listings
bicycle -> bike_listing	1 : 1	Each listing is linked to one bicycle asset
brand / category -> bicycle	1 : N	Bicycles reference brand and category
bike_listing -> reservation	1 : N	A listing can have multiple reservations
reservation -> deposit	1 : 1	Each reservation is backed by one deposit
reservation -> transaction	1 : 1	Each reservation results in one transaction
transaction -> dispute	1 : 1	A transaction can have at most one dispute
dispute -> inspection_report	1 : 1	A dispute can have one inspection report
events -> event_bicycle	1 : N	An event hosts multiple bicycles
events -> event_inspector	1 : N	An event has multiple assigned inspectors
wallet -> wallet_transaction	1 : N	A wallet has many balance change records

