5. Naming Conventions & Standards
The schema follows these consistent conventions:

Convention	Rule / Example
Primary Keys	All PKs are named <table_singular>_id (e.g. user_id, listing_id)
Foreign Keys	FK columns mirror the PK name of the referenced table
Timestamps	created_at / create_at for creation; updated_at / update_at for updates
Status fields	varchar ENUM-like columns (ACTIVE, PENDING, COMPLETED, CANCELLED, etc.)
Table naming	Lowercase snake_case (bike_listing, wallet_transaction)
Column naming	Lowercase snake_case (full_name, year_manufacture)
Unique FKs	UNIQUE constraint on FK = enforces 1-to-1 relationship
Double precision	Used for all monetary amounts and GPS coordinates

