BicycleExchange
Field-Level Data Dictionary
Describes the purpose and function of every field in all 20 tables  |  March 2026

Introduction
This document provides a field-level data dictionary for the BicycleExchange database. For each of the 20 tables, every column is documented with its data type, key/constraint status, and a detailed description of its business function — what it stores, why it exists, and how it is used by the application.

Group 1: User & Authentication
1. users
Central user account table. Every actor on the platform — buyer, seller, inspector, and admin — has a record here. The role field determines what actions a user is permitted to perform.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
user_id	integer	PK	Auto-incremented unique identifier for each user. Used as the primary reference key across all tables that involve a user.
username	varchar		The unique login handle chosen by the user. Used for authentication and display purposes.
password	varchar		Stores the bcrypt-hashed password. Never stored in plain text. Used during credential-based login.
full_name	varchar		The user's real full name as registered. Displayed on listings, reservations, and check-in records.
phone	varchar		Contact phone number. Used for buyer-seller communication coordination and check-in verification.
email	varchar		Email address used for account registration, notifications, and password recovery.
role	varchar		Defines the user's permission level on the platform. Accepted values: BUYER, SELLER, INSPECTOR, ADMIN. Controls what features and endpoints the user can access.
status	varchar		Current account status. Accepted values: ACTIVE (normal), INACTIVE (self-deactivated), BANNED (admin-suspended). Controls login eligibility.
address	varchar		Physical address of the user. Used for profile display and optionally for logistics.
avatar	varchar		URL pointing to the user's profile picture stored in object storage. Displayed throughout the UI.
google_id	varchar		Google OAuth2 subject ID. Populated when user registers or logs in via Google Sign-In. NULL for credential-only accounts.
created_at	date		Date the account was first created. Used for analytics and audit purposes.
create_date	date		Alternative creation date field. May reflect the date the profile was completed as opposed to initial registration.

2. wallet
Each user has exactly one wallet record. The wallet holds the user's platform balance which is used to pay deposits, receive sale proceeds, and pay/receive refunds.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
wallet_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for the wallet record.
balance	double	NOT NULL	Current available balance in VND. Updated atomically whenever a wallet_transaction is recorded. This is the authoritative balance figure.
username	varchar		Denormalized copy of the owner's username. Stored here for fast display without joining to users.
type	varchar		Wallet type indicator. Distinguishes between USER wallets and the platform's own SYSTEM wallet used to hold service fees.
updated_at	timestamp		Timestamp of the last balance change. Used to detect stale data and for audit trails.
user_id	integer	FK, UNIQUE	References users.user_id. The UNIQUE constraint enforces the 1-to-1 relationship — each user can have only one wallet.

3. wallet_transaction
Immutable ledger of every balance movement in every wallet. Each row represents one atomic change — a top-up, withdrawal, fee deduction, refund, or transfer. The running balance is stored for quick balance reconstruction.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
wallet_trans_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for the ledger entry.
amount	double	NOT NULL	The monetary amount involved in this transaction (VND). Always a positive number; the type field determines direction.
type	varchar		Direction and reason for the balance change. Values: DEPOSIT (top-up), WITHDRAWAL, REFUND, FEE (platform fee deducted), TRANSFER (peer payment).
description	varchar		Human-readable explanation of this entry, e.g. 'Deposit for listing #42' or 'Platform fee for sale #7'.
balance	double		Wallet balance immediately after this transaction was applied. Enables balance reconstruction without summing all rows.
create_at	timestamp		Exact timestamp this entry was created. Used for chronological ledger display and auditing.
wallet_id	integer	FK	References wallet.wallet_id. Identifies which wallet this entry belongs to.

4. invalidate_token
JWT token blacklist. When a user logs out or a token is revoked, the token string is inserted here. The authentication middleware checks this table on every request to reject invalidated tokens before they naturally expire.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
id	varchar	PK	The raw JWT token string used as the primary key. Allows O(1) lookup by the auth middleware to determine if a token has been revoked.
expiry_date	timestamp		The token's original expiry timestamp. A background cleanup job uses this to purge rows that are already past expiry, keeping the table small.

Group 2: Bicycle Catalog
5. brand
Simple reference table for bicycle manufacturers. Normalized to avoid duplicating brand names across listings and to enable brand-based filtering.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
brand_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for the brand.
name	varchar		Brand name (e.g. Trek, Giant, Specialized, Merida). Displayed on listing pages and used as a search/filter dimension.

6. category
Reference table for bicycle categories. Enables consistent classification of bicycles for browsing, filtering, and event organization.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
category_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for the category.
name	varchar		Category display name shown to users (e.g. Road Bike, Mountain Bike, Folding Bike).
bicycle_type	varchar		Machine-readable bicycle type code used internally for filtering and event bike_type matching.

7. bicycle
Stores the complete technical specification of each physical bicycle registered on the platform. One bicycle asset = one row. This table is the source of truth for what the bike actually is, independent of its listing status.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
bike_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for the bicycle asset.
bike_type	varchar		Category of bicycle: Road, Mountain (MTB), Hybrid, Folding, BMX, etc.
brake_type	varchar		Brake system: Rim, Disc Hydraulic, Disc Mechanical, V-Brake, Coaster, etc.
color	varchar		Primary color of the bicycle frame. Used for display and buyer filtering.
drivetrain	varchar		Drivetrain configuration: Single Speed, 1x, 2x, 3x, or specific groupset name.
fork_type	varchar		Fork classification: Rigid, Suspension (travel in mm), Carbon, etc.
frame_material	varchar		Material the frame is made of: Aluminum, Carbon Fiber, Steel, Titanium, Chromoly.
frame_size	varchar		Frame size in cm or S/M/L/XL notation. Critical for buyer fit.
number_of_gears	varchar	NOT NULL	Total number of gear combinations (e.g. 21, 18, 1 for single speed). Required field for all listings.
wheel_size	varchar		Wheel diameter in inches or mm (e.g. 26", 27.5", 700c, 29"). Important for compatibility.
year_manufacture	integer	NOT NULL	Year the bicycle was manufactured. Required. Used to calculate age and affects pricing suggestions.
chain	varchar		Chain brand and spec (e.g. KMC X11, Shimano CN-HG601). Indicates drivetrain compatibility.
chainring	varchar		Chainring tooth count or brand/model (e.g. 50/34T, FSA Gossamer). Indicates gearing.
fork	varchar		Specific fork brand/model name (e.g. Fox 32 Rhythm, RockShox Judy). More detailed than fork_type.
handlebar	varchar		Handlebar type and spec: Drop Bar, Flat Bar, Riser Bar, brand/model name.
rim	varchar		Rim brand and model (e.g. Mavic Open Pro, DT Swiss R470). Indicates wheel quality.
saddle	varchar		Saddle brand and model (e.g. Selle Italia X1, Fizik Aliante). Affects comfort assessment.
shock_absorber	varchar		Rear shock details for full-suspension bikes (e.g. Fox Float DPS, RockShox Monarch). NULL for hardtails.
weight	double		Total bicycle weight in kilograms. Important buying consideration for road and performance bikes.
bike_condition	integer		Numeric condition score (e.g. 1–10 or 1–5 scale). Set by seller or inspector; affects listing visibility and price.
brand_id	integer	FK -> brand	References brand.brand_id. Associates this bicycle with a manufacturer brand.
category_id	integer	FK -> category	References category.category_id. Classifies this bicycle into a browsable category.

8. bicycle_library
A curated reference library of standard bicycle models. Used as an auto-fill source when sellers create new listings — they can pick a model from this library and have the spec fields pre-populated, reducing data entry errors.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for the library entry.
model	varchar		Official model name of the bicycle (e.g. Trek Domane SL 6, Giant TCR Advanced 1). The primary search field in this table.
bike_type	varchar		Bicycle category type for this model.
brake_type	varchar		Factory default brake system for this model.
color	varchar		Standard colorway(s) available for this model.
drivetrain	varchar		Stock drivetrain configuration.
fork_type	varchar		Stock fork type.
frame_material	varchar		Frame material as shipped from the factory.
frame_size	varchar		Available frame sizes for this model.
number_of_gears	varchar		Stock gear count.
wheel_size	varchar		Stock wheel size.
year_manufacture	integer	NOT NULL	Model year this library entry represents. Required to differentiate between annual revisions of the same model.
chain	varchar		Stock chain spec.
chainring	varchar		Stock chainring spec.
fork	varchar		Stock fork brand/model.
handlebar	varchar		Stock handlebar type.
rim	varchar		Stock rim brand/model.
saddle	varchar		Stock saddle brand/model.
shock_absorber	varchar		Stock rear shock (if applicable).
weight	double		Official manufacturer-stated weight in kg.
brand_id	integer	FK -> brand	References brand.brand_id. Associates this library entry with a manufacturer.
category_id	integer	FK -> category	References category.category_id. Classifies this model.

Group 3: Listings & Wishlist
9. bike_listing
The marketplace listing created by a seller to advertise a bicycle for sale. A listing wraps a bicycle asset with commercial details (price, description, images) and a lifecycle status. The core entity of the online marketplace.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
listing_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for the listing.
title	varchar		Seller-written headline for the listing (e.g. '2021 Trek Emonda SL 5 - Excellent Condition'). The primary text shown in search results.
description	varchar		Detailed free-text description written by the seller. Covers condition, history, included accessories, reason for selling, etc.
image_url	varchar		URL of the primary listing photo. May be a comma-separated list or a JSON array if multiple images are supported.
price	double	NOT NULL	Asking price in VND set by the seller. Required. Displayed prominently and used as the basis for deposit calculation.
condition	varchar		Seller-stated condition label: NEW, LIKE NEW, GOOD, FAIR, POOR. Supplements the numeric bike_condition score.
status	varchar		Listing lifecycle status: AVAILABLE (open for offers), RESERVED (deposit paid, pending transaction), SOLD (completed), CLOSED (delisted by seller).
created_at	timestamp		Timestamp when the listing was first published.
updated_at	timestamp		Timestamp of the most recent edit to listing details.
bicycle_id	integer	FK, UNIQUE	References bicycle.bike_id. The UNIQUE constraint means one bicycle can only have one active listing at a time.
seller_id	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id. Identifies the seller who owns and is responsible for this listing.

10. wishlist
Records which listings a user has saved/favorited. Enables buyers to track bicycles they are interested in without committing to a reservation.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
wishlist_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for the wishlist entry.
listing_id	integer	FK -> bike_listing	References bike_listing.listing_id. The listing that was saved.
user_id	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id. The user who saved this listing.

Group 4: Events
11. events
Physical bicycle marketplace events organized by platform admins. Events provide a venue where multiple sellers exhibit their bicycles simultaneously and buyers can inspect them in person before purchasing.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
event_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for the event.
name	varchar		Public-facing event name (e.g. 'HCM Bike Fair – Q1 2026'). Displayed in event listings.
type	varchar		Event format type, e.g. OPEN_MARKET, AUCTION, EXHIBITION. Controls event workflow.
bike_type	varchar		The primary bicycle category the event focuses on (e.g. Road, MTB, All). Used for buyer targeting.
location	varchar		Venue name or landmark description (e.g. 'Tao Dan Park, District 1').
address	varchar		Full street address of the event venue.
latitude	double		GPS latitude of the venue. Used to render the event on a map.
longitude	double		GPS longitude of the venue. Used to render the event on a map.
status	varchar		Event lifecycle status: DRAFT (being prepared), PUBLISHED (visible to public), ONGOING (currently happening), COMPLETED, CANCELLED.
create_date	date		Date the event record was created by the admin.
public_date	date		Date the event becomes visible to sellers and buyers on the platform. Allows advance scheduling.
start_date	date		Official start date of the physical event.
end_date	date		Official end date of the physical event.
update_date	date		Date of the last modification to the event record.
create_by	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id of the admin who created this event. Establishes accountability.

12. event_bicycle
Represents a bicycle that a seller has registered to exhibit and sell at a specific event. A bridge between a seller's existing listing and an event, with event-specific pricing and status.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
event_bike_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for this event-bicycle registration.
title	varchar		Display title for this bicycle at the event. May differ from the original listing title.
bike_type	varchar		Bicycle type, copied from the listing for quick filtering at the event level.
type	varchar		Entry type, e.g. SALE (available for purchase), DISPLAY (exhibition only).
seller_name	varchar		Seller's display name, denormalized here for quick rendering on event booth displays.
price	double		Event-specific asking price. May differ from the original listing price — sellers can set a special event price.
condition	varchar		Condition label at the time of event registration.
image_url	varchar		Primary image URL for display at the event.
status	varchar		Registration status: PENDING (awaiting admin approval), APPROVED, REJECTED, SOLD, CANCELLED.
create_date	date		Date the seller submitted this registration.
update_date	date		Date the registration was last updated.
event_id	integer	FK -> events	References events.event_id. Identifies which event this bicycle is registered for.
listing_id	integer	FK -> bike_listing	References bike_listing.listing_id. Links back to the original online listing.
bike_id	integer	FK -> bicycle	References bicycle.bike_id. Direct link to the physical bicycle asset.
user_id	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id. The seller who registered this bicycle for the event.

13. event_inspector
Manages inspector assignments to events. Inspectors assigned here are available at the event venue to evaluate bicycles during check-in and resolve disputes on-site.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
inspec_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for this inspector assignment.
status	varchar		Assignment status: PENDING (invited), CONFIRMED (accepted), DECLINED, COMPLETED.
create_date	timestamp		Timestamp when the assignment was created.
event_id	integer	FK -> events	References events.event_id. The event this inspector is assigned to.
user_id	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id of the inspector. The user must have role = INSPECTOR.

Group 5: Transaction Lifecycle
14. deposit
Records a deposit payment made by a buyer to express serious intent to purchase. The deposit locks the listing or event bicycle and triggers the reservation process. It can later be applied to the final sale, refunded (if seller cancels), or forfeited (if buyer cancels).

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
deposit_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for this deposit record.
amount	double	NOT NULL	Deposit amount in VND. Typically a percentage of the asking price, defined by system_config.
type	varchar		Deposit context: LISTING (for a direct marketplace purchase) or EVENT (for a purchase at an event).
status	varchar		Current state: PENDING (initiated), PAID (funds held), APPLIED (used in final transaction), REFUNDED (returned to buyer), FORFEITED (transferred to seller).
created_at	timestamp		Timestamp when the deposit was initiated.
listing_id	integer	FK -> bike_listing	References bike_listing.listing_id. Populated for non-event deposits. NULL for event deposits.
event_bike_id	integer	FK -> event_bicycle	References event_bicycle.event_bike_id. Populated for event deposits. NULL for listing deposits.
user_id	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id. The buyer who made this deposit.

15. reservation
A confirmed meeting arrangement between buyer and seller. Created after a deposit is paid. Captures all logistics of the in-person meeting including location, time, and assigned inspector.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
reservation_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for the reservation.
status	varchar		Reservation lifecycle: PENDING (waiting for confirmation), CONFIRMED (both parties agreed), COMPLETED (meeting happened), CANCELLED.
deposit_amount	double		Snapshot of the deposit amount at the time of reservation creation. Preserved for record even if deposit record changes.
meeting_location	varchar		Text description of the agreed meeting location, e.g. '1st floor, Landmark 81, Binh Thanh'.
meeting_time	timestamp		Scheduled date and time for the buyer-seller meeting.
latitude	double		GPS latitude of the meeting point. Enables map display of the meeting location.
longitude	double		GPS longitude of the meeting point.
cancel_description	varchar		Free-text explanation provided when a reservation is cancelled. Required on cancellation.
cancel_image	varchar		URL of an uploaded evidence image supporting the cancellation reason.
reserved_at	timestamp		Timestamp when the reservation was first created.
buyer_id	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id. The buyer who initiated this reservation.
inspector_id	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id of the assigned inspector. The inspector who will be present at the meeting to verify the bicycle.
listing_id	integer	FK -> bike_listing	References bike_listing.listing_id. The listing this reservation is for (for non-event purchases).
event_bike_id	integer	FK -> event_bicycle	References event_bicycle.event_bike_id. The event bicycle this reservation is for (for event purchases).
deposit_id	integer	FK, UNIQUE	References deposit.deposit_id. The UNIQUE constraint enforces 1-to-1: one reservation = one deposit.

16. check_in
Records the physical verification event when buyer and seller arrive at the agreed meeting point. The inspector verifies identities using a shared token before the sale proceeds.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
check_in_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for this check-in record.
buyer_name	varchar		Buyer's name as verified at check-in time. Snapshotted for audit purposes.
buyer_phone	varchar		Buyer's phone number verified at check-in.
seller_name	varchar		Seller's name as verified at check-in time.
seller_phone	varchar		Seller's phone number verified at check-in.
token	varchar		One-time verification token generated for this meeting. Both buyer and seller must present this token to the inspector to confirm their identities.
status	varchar		Check-in status: PENDING, BUYER_CHECKED (buyer arrived), COMPLETED (both arrived), FAILED (one party no-showed).
buyer_id	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id. The buyer participating in this check-in.
seller_id	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id. The seller participating in this check-in.
reservation_id	integer	FK -> reservation	References reservation.reservation_id. The reservation this check-in belongs to.
event_bike_id	integer	FK -> event_bicycle	References event_bicycle.event_bike_id. The event bicycle being checked in (for event transactions).
listing_id	integer	FK -> bike_listing	References bike_listing.listing_id. The listing being checked in (for non-event transactions).

17. transaction
The final financial record of a completed bicycle sale. Created when both buyer and seller confirm the check-in and the inspector approves the bicycle. The platform fee is deducted and proceeds are released to the seller's wallet.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
transaction_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for the transaction.
actual_price	double	NOT NULL	The final agreed sale price in VND. May differ from the original listing price if negotiated.
amount	double	NOT NULL	Amount transferred from buyer's wallet to seller's wallet (actual_price minus fee).
fee	double	NOT NULL	Platform service fee deducted from the transaction amount. Calculated based on system_config fee rate.
type	varchar		Transaction context: LISTING (direct online sale) or EVENT (sale at a physical event).
status	varchar		Transaction status: PENDING, COMPLETED, CANCELLED, REFUNDED.
description	varchar		Auto-generated or manually set description summarizing the transaction.
create_at	timestamp		Timestamp when the transaction was initiated.
update_at	timestamp		Timestamp of the most recent status update.
buyer_id	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id. The buyer in this transaction.
seller_id	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id. The seller receiving payment.
listing_id	integer	FK -> bike_listing	References bike_listing.listing_id. The listing that was sold.
event_id	integer	FK -> events	References events.event_id. The event where the sale occurred (NULL for non-event sales).
event_bike_id	integer	FK -> event_bicycle	References event_bicycle.event_bike_id. The event bicycle record (NULL for non-event sales).
deposit_id	integer	FK, UNIQUE	References deposit.deposit_id. UNIQUE — links this transaction to the deposit that initiated the process.
reservation_id	integer	FK, UNIQUE	References reservation.reservation_id. UNIQUE — one transaction per reservation.

18. dispute
Records a formal dispute raised by either the buyer or seller against a transaction. An inspector is assigned to investigate and resolve the issue. Disputes can result in refunds, forfeitures, or confirmation of the original transaction.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
dispute_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for the dispute.
reason	varchar		Free-text explanation written by the user who raised the dispute describing what went wrong.
reason_category	varchar	CHECK	Standardized category of the dispute issue. Allowed values: MISDESCRIPTION, NON_DELIVERY, BUYER_DEFAULT, DAMAGE_ON_DELIVERY, PAYMENT_ISSUE, CANCELLATION, OTHER. The CHECK constraint enforces this enum.
status	varchar		Dispute resolution status: OPEN (just raised), UNDER_REVIEW (inspector assigned), RESOLVED (decision made), CLOSED.
created_at	timestamp		Timestamp when the dispute was raised.
raised_by	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id. The user (buyer or seller) who initiated the dispute.
assigned_inspector_id	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id of the inspector assigned to investigate and resolve this dispute.
transaction_id	integer	FK, UNIQUE	References transaction.transaction_id. UNIQUE — each transaction can have at most one dispute.

19. inspection_report
The formal evaluation report submitted by an inspector. Can be filed during a reservation (pre-sale bicycle check) or as part of a dispute resolution investigation.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
report_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for the inspection report.
result	varchar		Overall inspection outcome: PASS (bicycle matches description, sale proceeds), FAIL (significant issues found, sale halted), CONDITIONAL (minor issues noted, sale may proceed with disclosure).
checklist_items	text		JSON-encoded array of individual checklist items and their pass/fail status. Covers frame, brakes, drivetrain, wheels, saddle, handlebars, etc.
note	varchar		Inspector's free-text notes and observations during the inspection.
reason	varchar		Specific reason for the inspection result, especially used when result is FAIL or CONDITIONAL.
created_at	timestamp		Timestamp when the inspector submitted this report.
inspector_id	integer	FK -> users	References users.user_id. The inspector who performed the inspection and authored this report.
reservation_id	integer	FK -> reservation	References reservation.reservation_id. Links this report to the reservation it was filed for (pre-sale inspection).
dispute_id	integer	FK, UNIQUE	References dispute.dispute_id. UNIQUE — one inspection report per dispute. Populated only for dispute-related inspections.

Group 6: Platform Management
20. system_config
A key-value store for platform-wide numeric configuration parameters. Allows admins to tune business rules without code changes — for example, adjusting the deposit percentage or platform fee rate.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
config_id	integer	PK	Unique identifier for the configuration entry.
key	varchar		Machine-readable configuration key name (e.g. DEPOSIT_RATE, PLATFORM_FEE_RATE, MIN_LISTING_PRICE). Read by application services at runtime.
value	double	NOT NULL	Numeric value for this configuration. For rates, stored as decimal (e.g. 0.10 = 10%). For amounts, stored in VND.
description	varchar		Human-readable explanation of what this config key controls and what the value represents. Displayed in the admin panel.

21. invalidate_token
JWT token blacklist used to enforce logout and token revocation without waiting for natural token expiry.

Field Name	Data Type	Key / Constraint	Field Function & Description
id	varchar	PK	The raw JWT token string stored as the primary key. On every authenticated API request, the auth middleware checks if the incoming token exists here. If found, the request is rejected as unauthorized.
expiry_date	timestamp		The expiry timestamp embedded in the JWT. A scheduled background job periodically deletes rows where expiry_date is in the past, keeping this table lean.

